# Turnberry Place â€” Integrity & Architecture Patterns

Established 2026-04-18 across commits `76bc393` â†’ `eb6595d`. These patterns
are non-negotiable for this repo and supersede generic 2026 best-practice
defaults where they conflict.

## 1. Reviews / GBP CTA â€” env-gated, no fabrication

**Rule:** All "View Google Reviews" / "Write a Review" CTAs route through
`lib/reviews.ts`. Never hardcode a `place_id`, `placeid=ChIJâ€¦`,
`g.page/r/â€¦`, or `google.com/maps/place/?q=place_id:â€¦` in any component.

**Precedence (highest wins):**
1. `NEXT_PUBLIC_GBP_REVIEWS_URL` â€” full read URL (env var, Vercel)
2. `NEXT_PUBLIC_GBP_WRITEREVIEW_URL` â€” full write URL
3. `NEXT_PUBLIC_GBP_PLACE_ID` â€” bare `ChIJâ€¦` ID (helper builds both URLs)
4. **Fallback:** Google Maps URL API search action built from
   `CANONICAL_NAP` in `lib/reviews.ts`

**Operator off-switch:** `NEXT_PUBLIC_GBP_REVIEWS_DISABLED=true` hides
both CTAs site-wide without a code change. Always set this during a GBP
verification window so visitors don't land on disambiguation pages.

**Multi-GBP awareness:** Dr. Jan Duffy operates **multiple distinct GBPs**
(at minimum: Arts District / Centennial Hills / Sunset / Sahara /
MacDonald Highlands / 2827 Paradise Rd). Before changing `CANONICAL_NAP`,
confirm with the operator which GBP this site targets. The current
target is the new GBP at 2827 Paradise Rd: **`Turnberry Place | Condos
by Dr. Jan Duffy`**.

## 2. AggregateRating â€” env-gated, validated, no fabrication

**Rule:** Use `lib/schema/aggregateRating.ts` `buildAggregateRating()`.
Never hardcode `aggregateRating`, `ratingValue`, `reviewCount`,
`bestRating`, or `worstRating` anywhere in JSON-LD.

Helper requires BOTH `NEXT_PUBLIC_GBP_AGGREGATE_RATING_VALUE` and
`NEXT_PUBLIC_GBP_AGGREGATE_RATING_COUNT` to be set AND valid (1â€“5,
positive integer). Invalid values silently emit nothing â€” never ship a
malformed schema.

Currently wired into `RealEstateAgent` and `ApartmentComplex` schemas.
If adding it elsewhere, spread conditionally:

```ts
const aggregateRating = buildAggregateRating()
return { ..., ...(aggregateRating ? { aggregateRating } : {}) }
```

## 3. Build-stable dates â€” never `new Date()` in render or schema

**Rule:** Any `<time>` attribute, "Last updated" copy, JSON-LD
`datePublished` / `dateModified` / `uploadDate`, sitemap `<lastmod>`,
or freshness indicator MUST use a constant from `lib/build-date.ts`:

- `BUILD_DATE_ISO` â€” for ISO-8601 (schema, `<time dateTime>`, sitemap)
- `BUILD_DATE_DISPLAY` â€” for human "April 18, 2026" copy
- `BUILD_DATE_MONTH_YEAR` â€” for coarse "April 2026" labels

**Why:** `new Date()` evaluated during SSR (Vercel UTC) vs. client
hydration (visitor TZ) causes React #423/#425 hydration errors and
client-only re-renders. In sitemaps, dynamic dates trigger Google's
"lastmod inflation" distrust pattern. Fixed once in commit `63544df`.

If you genuinely need a runtime current time (e.g. countdown timer),
defer to `useEffect` after mount â€” see `components/live-inventory-badge.tsx`.

## 4. Empty-state-safe components â€” fabrication-impossible-by-construction

**Rule:** Components that display social proof, stats, press mentions,
or reviews MUST be prop-driven with empty-state defaults. Never
hardcode social-proof claims in component bodies.

Reference implementations (commit `ca26581`):
- `components/power-of-numbers.tsx` â€” returns `null` when `stats=[]`
- `components/in-the-media.tsx` â€” returns `null` when `items=[]`,
  filters out items missing `url`
- `components/why-work-with-us.tsx` â€” only verifiable claims (BHHS
  affiliation, license number, multi-office footprint), no numerics

**Type-level enforcement:** Required fields like `MediaItem.url` and
`PowerStat.sourceNote` make verifiable backing structurally mandatory
at the call site.

## 5. Multi-GBP NAP â€” visible NAP may diverge from GBP NAP

The site's footer presentation NAP (`Turnberry Place | 2827 Paradise
Rd, Las Vegas, NV 89109`) is deliberate â€” that's where tours happen.
The GBP NAP that drives Google entity resolution lives in
`lib/reviews.ts` `CANONICAL_NAP`. They CAN diverge if the operator
intends it. Document any divergence inline with rationale; do not
silently align them.

## 6. label-content-name-mismatch â€” no redundant `aria-label`

**Rule:** When an interactive element has visible text, do NOT add an
`aria-label` that duplicates or fails-to-contain the visible text.
WCAG 2.5.3 + axe `label-content-name-mismatch` will flag it.

**Pattern for "opens in new tab" cues:**

```tsx
<a href={calendlyUrl} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
  Schedule Tour
  <span className="sr-only"> (opens Calendly in a new tab)</span>
</a>
```

The visible text becomes the accessible name; the sr-only span adds
context without breaking substring-containment. Established in commit
`44221c4` (label-sweep) and reinforced in `d720592` (testimonials).

## 7. FAQ accordions â€” native `<details>` / `<summary>`

**Rule:** Use HTML-native `<details>` / `<summary>` for collapsible
FAQ items. Don't reach for a JS state machine. Reference: `pages/photos.tsx`
plus `.photos-faq-item` styles in `styles/components.css`.

Native disclosure has full keyboard + screen-reader support free, plus
`open` attribute is part of the DOM (selectable in CSS). Pair the
visible Q&A with a `FAQPage` JSON-LD block so visible content and
schema stay in lockstep.

## 8. Schema entity consolidation â€” `isPartOf` for child pages

**Rule:** Sub-pages that emit their own JSON-LD entity (e.g.
`ImageGallery` on `/photos`) MUST declare `isPartOf` pointing at the
parent `ApartmentComplex` `@id` from the home page:

```ts
isPartOf: {
  '@type': 'ApartmentComplex',
  '@id': `${baseUrl}/#apartmentcomplex`,
}
```

Tells Google these pages are children of one entity, not separate
entities. Established in commit `2b83ddb` for `/photos`.

## 9. Stale planning docs â€” banner, don't delete

When a `.md` file at repo root contains fabricated stats, stale phone
numbers, deprecated tech references, or "all complete" framing that no
longer matches reality:

1. Do **not** delete (per repo "never delete files without approval" rule).
2. Add a warning banner at the top: blockquote starting with
   `> âš ď¸Ź **HISTORICAL PLANNING DOCUMENT â€” DO NOT TREAT AS SOURCE OF
   TRUTH**` that lists specific issues by name and points to current
   sources (`CLAUDE.md`, `git log`, source files).

Reference commit: `f9309f0`. Files currently bannered:
`JILLS_ZEDER_FEATURES.md`, `HOMEPAGE_OPTIMIZATION_SUMMARY.md`,
`PROJECT_COMPLETE.md`.

## 10. robots.txt â€” explicit AI-crawler + social-preview allowlist

**Rule:** Even though `User-agent: *` allow-all covers all bots,
maintain explicit `Allow` entries for the canonical 2026 AI-training
and social-preview crawlers. Makes intent scannable for auditors.
Current canonical list (commit `eb6595d`): Googlebot, Bingbot, GPTBot,
CCBot, PerplexityBot, ClaudeBot, Google-Extended, Applebot-Extended,
Applebot, anthropic-ai, DuckAssistBot, Meta-ExternalAgent, Amazonbot,
Bytespider, facebookexternalhit, Twitterbot, LinkedInBot.

Never add `Disallow: /_next/static` â€” Google needs it to render JS-heavy
pages and will downrank if blocked.

